Steps.Message: Update at 03:21 - Our engineers have completed investigations. There's a lot of work required on site to repair a fault on a section of overhead cables in the Felcourt Road, RH19 2 area, so we have decided to use temporary generators to provide power. To allow time for us to get the generators out to your area and connect them, we're estimating we'll have power back on between 10:30 and 11:30. We will now need to send out a relief team first thing in the morning to connect them up. This means that you may not receive any texts for a while. We'll let you know as soon as the team are on their way.

We became aware of this power cut at 22:29. We’re sorry for any disruption this may have caused you. We didn’t know in advance there would be a power cut, but now that we know, our teams will do everything they can to get your power back quickly. Engineers in our control room have switched some customers power back on in your area. To get everyone’s power back on we may need to attend to investigate and make repairs. We’ll continue to update you until everyone’s power is back on.
Steps.Name: We are restoring customers automatically

Steps.Message: We have engineers on their way. As this is affecting your area, they will not need to attend your property. Rest assured once they arrive, they’ll work as quickly as is safely possible to get your power back on.
Steps.Name: Engineers on their way

Steps.Message: Engineers are now on site, carrying out investigations into the fault. Once they have completed their assessment, they will carry out repairs.
Steps.Name: Engineers investigating and fixing
